benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/xml - Upload the full catalog as XML

covered: Valid Payload coverage: Multiple scenarios confirm successful POST with valid catalog XML across varying header presence (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC11, TC15, TC18, TC21, TC22, TC24, TC25, TC26, TC27, TC28, TC29, TC30, TC31).
Invalid Payload handling: Tests for malformed XML, empty body, whitespace-only payload, and invalid content type (TC08, TC09, TC07, TC10, TC12, TC16).
Header validation and authorization: Tests for missing and empty X-Killbill-CreatedBy, optional headers, and authentication/authorization scenarios (TC06, TC07, TC02, TC14).
Error handling and server availability: Scenarios covering 400 due to invalid input, 503 due to backend/service unavailability (TC16, TC08, TC09, TC10).
Boundary, encoding, and content robustness: Tests for large payloads, different encodings, whitespace, comments/CDATA, boundary values (TC12, TC13, TC29, TC30, TC28, TC27).
Performance scenarios: 10 sequential requests and 20 concurrent requests (TC19, TC20).
Regression and backward compatibility: Known-bug regression and legacy-client scenarios (TC21, TC22).
Duplicate submission handling: Duplicate version scenario (TC25).
Content-type and unexpected headers: Unknown/extra headers scenarios (TC11, TC26).
gaps: Caching behavior not tested (ETag/Cache-Control) for POST responses.
Explicit rate-limiting/throttling tests not present (beyond general performance tests).
Explicit 422 or more granular error codes for some security/content checks are not defined (only 400/403/401 mentioned in places).
Some tests imply behavior for very large-scale edge cases (e.g., extreme concurrency or ultra-large payloads) but explicit dedicated stress/soak tests are limited to TC19/TC20.
recommendations: Add explicit caching validation tests (ETag/Cache-Control headers) for POST to ensure proper caching semantics where applicable.
Introduce explicit rate-limiting/throttling tests to validate behavior under bursts (beyond existing TC19/TC20).
Expand error-code coverage to include additional granular responses (e.g., 422 for invalid content or validation failures, where applicable).
Consider additional security-focused tests for XML payloads to further validate against XXE and other XML-related vulnerabilities (beyond TC17).
Add targeted tests for edge-case payload sizes approaching system limits and document the exact thresholds.
